#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:78
msgid "Version 26.5.1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:82
msgid ""
"Fix unstable formatting of annotated assignments whose subscript annotation "
"contains an inline comment (e.g. `x: list[  # pyright: ignore[...]`) ([#5130]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/5130))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:84
msgid ""
"Preserve inline comments (including `# type: ignore`) immediately before a "
"`# fmt: skip` line, avoiding AST equivalence failures ([#5139](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/5139))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:89
msgid ""
"Correct the version in the published executables ([#5137](https://github.com/"
"psf/black/pull/5137))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:93
msgid ""
"Add Neovim integration guide covering conform.nvim, ALE, and simple command "
"approaches ([#5124](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/5124))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:96
msgid "Version 26.5.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:100
msgid ""
"Add support for unpacking in comprehensions (PEP 798) and for lazy imports "
"(PEP 810), both new syntactic features in Python 3.15 ([#5048](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/5048))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:102
msgid ""
"Python 3.15 is now supported. Compiled wheels are not yet provided for "
"Python 3.15, so performance may be slower than on existing Python versions. "
"Wheels will be provided once Python 3.15 is later in its release cycle. "
"([#5127](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/5127))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:108
msgid ""
"Fix `# fmt: skip` being ignored in nested `if` expressions with "
"parenthesized `in` clauses ([#4903](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/4903))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:110
msgid ""
"Add syntactic support for Python 3.15 ([#5048](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/5048))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:111
msgid ""
"Fix crash when an f-string follows a `# fmt: off` comment inside brackets "
"([#5097](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/5097))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:112
msgid ""
"Preserve multiline compound statement headers when `# fmt: skip` is placed "
"on the colon line ([#5117](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/5117))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:117
msgid ""
"Improve heuristics around whether blank lines should appear before, within "
"and after groups of same-name decorated functions (such as `@overload` "
"groups) in `.pyi` stub files ([#5021](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/5021))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:120
msgid ""
"Fix blank lines being removed between a function and a decorated class in `."
"pyi` stub files ([#5092](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/5092))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:122
msgid ""
"Prevent string merger from creating unsplittable long lines when a pragma "
"comment (e.g. `# type: ignore`) follows the closing bracket ([#5096](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/5096))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:127
msgid "Run CI on 3.15 ([#5127](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/5127))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:131
msgid ""
"Improve parse error readability by showing multi-line output with an error "
"pointer. ([#5068](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/5068))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:133
msgid ""
"Add `SourceASTParseError` to distinguish source parse failures from internal "
"safety errors, improving error reporting when Black's lenient parser accepts "
"input that `ast.parse()` rejects ([#5080](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/5080))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:139
msgid ""
"Return HTTP 400 (Bad Request) for source parse failures instead of HTTP 500, "
"keeping HTTP 500 only for genuine internal safety errors ([#5080](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/5080))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:144
msgid ""
"Added documentation for doctest formatting tools and updated the "
"integrations index to match ([#4916](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/4916))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:149
msgid ""
"Use \"Version X.Y.Z\" headings in changelog for stable permalink anchors on "
"ReadTheDocs ([#5063](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/5063))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:151
msgid ""
"Note in the editor integrations that the SublimeText `sublack` plugin is "
"archived and unmaintained ([#5082](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/5082))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:154
msgid "Version 26.3.1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:158
msgid ""
"Prevent Jupyter notebook magic masking collisions from corrupting cells by "
"using exact-length placeholders for short magics and aborting if a "
"placeholder can no longer be unmasked safely ([#5038](https://github.com/psf/"
"black/pull/5038))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:164
msgid ""
"Always hash cache filename components derived from `--python-cell-magics` so "
"custom magic names cannot affect cache paths ([#5038](https://github.com/psf/"
"black/pull/5038))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:169
msgid ""
"Disable browser-originated requests by default, add configurable origin "
"allowlisting and request body limits, and bound executor submissions to "
"improve backpressure ([#5039](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/5039))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:173
msgid "Version 26.3.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:177
msgid ""
"Don't double-decode input, causing non-UTF-8 files to be corrupted ([#4964]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/4964))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:178
msgid ""
"Fix crash on standalone comment in lambda default arguments ([#4993](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/4993))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:179
msgid ""
"Preserve parentheses when `# type: ignore` comments would be merged with "
"other comments on the same line, preventing AST equivalence failures ([#4888]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/4888))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:184
msgid ""
"Fix bug where `if` guards in `case` blocks were incorrectly split when the "
"pattern had a trailing comma ([#4884](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/4884))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:186
msgid ""
"Fix `string_processing` crashing on unassigned long string literals with "
"trailing commas (one-item tuples) ([#4929](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/4929))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:188
msgid ""
"Simplify implementation of the power operator \"hugging\" logic ([#4918]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/4918))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:192
msgid ""
"Fix shutdown errors in PyInstaller builds on macOS by disabling "
"multiprocessing in frozen environments ([#4930](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/4930))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:197
msgid ""
"Introduce winloop for windows as an alternative to uvloop ([#4996](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/4996))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:198
msgid ""
"Remove deprecated function `uvloop.install()` in favor of `uvloop."
"new_event_loop()` ([#4996](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/4996))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:200
msgid ""
"Rename `maybe_install_uvloop` function to `maybe_use_uvloop` to simplify "
"loop installation and creation of either a uvloop/winloop eventloop or "
"default eventloop ([#4996](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/4996))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:206
msgid ""
"Emit a clear warning when the target Python version is newer than the "
"running Python version, since AST safety checks cannot parse newer syntax. "
"Also replace the misleading \"INTERNAL ERROR\" message with an actionable "
"error explaining the version mismatch ([#4983](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/4983))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:213
msgid ""
"Introduce winloop to be used when windows in use which enables blackd to run "
"faster on windows when winloop is installed. ([#4996](https://github.com/psf/"
"black/pull/4996))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:218
msgid ""
"Remove unused gallery script ([#5030](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/5030))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:219
msgid ""
"Harden parsing of `black` requirements in the GitHub Action when "
"`use_pyproject` is enabled so that only version specifiers are accepted and "
"direct references such as `black @ https://...` are rejected. Users should "
"upgrade to the latest version of the action as soon as possible. This update "
"is received automatically when using `psf/black@stable`, and is independent "
"of the version of Black installed by the action. ([#5031](https://github.com/"
"psf/black/pull/5031))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:228
msgid ""
"Expand preview style documentation with detailed examples for "
"`wrap_comprehension_in`, `simplify_power_operator_hugging`, and "
"`wrap_long_dict_values_in_parens` features ([#4987](https://github.com/psf/"
"black/pull/4987))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:231
msgid ""
"Add detailed documentation for formatting Jupyter Notebooks ([#5009](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/5009))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:233
msgid "Version 26.1.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:237
msgid ""
"Introduces the 2026 stable style ([#4892](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/4892)), stabilizing the following changes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:239
msgid ""
"`always_one_newline_after_import`: Always force one blank line after import "
"statements, except when the line after the import is a comment or an import "
"statement ([#4489](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/4489))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:242
msgid ""
"`fix_fmt_skip_in_one_liners`: Fix `# fmt: skip` behavior on one-liner "
"declarations, such as `def foo(): return \"mock\" # fmt: skip`, where "
"previously the declaration would have been incorrectly collapsed ([#4800]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/4800))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:245
msgid ""
"`fix_module_docstring_detection`: Fix module docstrings being treated as "
"normal strings if preceded by comments ([#4764](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/4764))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:247
msgid ""
"`fix_type_expansion_split`: Fix type expansions split in generic functions "
"([#4777](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/4777))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:248
msgid ""
"`multiline_string_handling`: Make expressions involving multiline strings "
"more compact ([#1879](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/1879))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:250
msgid ""
"`normalize_cr_newlines`: Add `\\r` style newlines to the potential newlines "
"to normalize file newlines both from and to ([#4710](https://github.com/psf/"
"black/pull/4710))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:252
msgid ""
"`remove_parens_around_except_types`: Remove parentheses around multiple "
"exception types in `except` and `except*` without `as` ([#4720](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/4720))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:254
msgid ""
"`remove_parens_from_assignment_lhs`: Remove unnecessary parentheses from the "
"left-hand side of assignments while preserving magic trailing commas and "
"intentional multiline formatting ([#4865](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/4865))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:257
msgid ""
"`standardize_type_comments`: Format type comments which have zero or more "
"spaces between `#` and `type:` or between `type:` and value to `# type: "
"(value)` ([#4645](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/4645))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:260
msgid "The following change was not in any previous stable release:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:262
msgid ""
"Regenerated the `_width_table.py` and added tests for the Khmer language "
"([#4253](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/4253))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:264
msgid ""
"This release alo bumps `pathspec` to v1 and fixes inconsistencies with Git's "
"`.gitignore` logic ([#4958](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/4958)). Now, "
"files will be ignored if a pattern matches them, even if the parent "
"directory is directly unignored. For example, Black would previously format "
"`exclude/not_this/foo.py` with this `.gitignore`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:269
msgid ""
"exclude/\n"
"!exclude/not_this/\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:274
msgid ""
"Now, `exclude/not_this/foo.py` will remain ignored. To ensure `exclude/"
"not_this/` and all of it's children are included in formatting (and in Git), "
"use this `.gitignore`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:277
msgid ""
"*/exclude/*\n"
"!*/exclude/not_this/\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:282
msgid ""
