msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1024
msgid ""
"Change verbose logging to exactly mirror _Black_'s logic for source "
"discovery ([#3749](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3749))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1028
msgid ""
"The `blackd` argument parser now shows the default values for options in "
"their help text ([#3712](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3712))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1033
msgid ""
"Black is now tested with [`PYTHONWARNDEFAULTENCODING = 1`](https://docs."
"python.org/3/library/io.html#io-encoding-warning) ([#3763](https://github."
"com/psf/black/pull/3763))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1036
msgid ""
"Update GitHub Action to display black output in the job summary ([#3688]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3688))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1040
msgid ""
"Add a CITATION.cff file to the root of the repository, containing metadata "
"on how to cite this software ([#3723](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/3723))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1042
msgid ""
"Update the _classes_ and _exceptions_ documentation in Developer reference "
"to match the latest code base ([#3755](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/3755))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1045
msgid "Version 23.3.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1049
msgid ""
"This release fixes a longstanding confusing behavior in Black's GitHub "
"action, where the version of the action did not determine the version of "
"Black being run (issue [#3382](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3382)). In "
"addition, there is a small bug fix around imports and a number of "
"improvements to the preview style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1054
msgid ""
"Please try out the [preview style](https://black.readthedocs.io/en/stable/"
"the_black_code_style/future_style.html#preview-style) with `black --preview` "
"and tell us your feedback. All changes in the preview style are expected to "
"become part of Black's stable style in January 2024."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1061
msgid ""
"Import lines with `# fmt: skip` and `# fmt: off` no longer have an extra "
"blank line added when they are right after another import line ([#3610]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3610))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1068
msgid ""
"`async def`, `async for`, and `async with` statements are now formatted "
"consistently compared to their non-async version. ([#3609](https://github."
"com/psf/black/pull/3609))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1070
msgid ""
"`with` statements that contain two context managers will be consistently "
"wrapped in parentheses ([#3589](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3589))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1072
msgid ""
"Let string splitters respect [East Asian Width](https://www.unicode.org/"
"reports/tr11/) ([#3445](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3445))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1074
msgid ""
"Now long string literals can be split after East Asian commas and periods "
"(`、` U+3001 IDEOGRAPHIC COMMA, `。` U+3002 IDEOGRAPHIC FULL STOP, & `，` "
"U+FF0C FULLWIDTH COMMA) besides before spaces ([#3445](https://github.com/"
"psf/black/pull/3445))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1077
msgid ""
"For stubs, enforce one blank line after a nested class with a body other "
"than just `...` ([#3564](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3564))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1079
msgid ""
"Improve handling of multiline strings by changing line split behavior "
"([#1879](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/1879))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1083
msgid ""
"Added support for formatting files with invalid type comments ([#3594]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3594))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1087
msgid ""
"Update GitHub Action to use the version of Black equivalent to action's "
"version if version input is not specified ([#3543](https://github.com/psf/"
"black/pull/3543))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1089
msgid ""
"Fix missing Python binary path in autoload script for vim ([#3508](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/3508))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1093
msgid ""
"Document that only the most recent release is supported for security issues; "
"vulnerabilities should be reported through Tidelift ([#3612](https://github."
"com/psf/black/pull/3612))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1096
msgid "Version 23.1.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1100
msgid ""
"This is the first release of 2023, and following our [stability policy]"
"(https://black.readthedocs.io/en/stable/the_black_code_style/index."
"html#stability-policy), it comes with a number of improvements to our stable "
"style, including improvements to empty line handling, removal of redundant "
"parentheses in several contexts, and output that highlights implicitly "
"concatenated strings better."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1106
msgid ""
"There are also many changes to the preview style; try out `black --preview` "
"and give us feedback to help us set the stable style for next year."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1109
msgid ""
"In addition to style changes, Black now automatically infers the supported "
"Python versions from your `pyproject.toml` file, removing the need to set "
"Black's target versions separately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1115
msgid ""
"Introduce the 2023 stable style, which incorporates most aspects of last "
"year's preview style ([#3418](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3418)). "
"Specific changes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1117
msgid ""
"Enforce empty lines before classes and functions with sticky leading "
"comments ([#3302](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3302)) (22.12.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1119
msgid ""
"Reformat empty and whitespace-only files as either an empty file (if no "
"newline is present) or as a single newline character (if a newline is "
"present) ([#3348](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3348)) (22.12.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1122
msgid ""
"Implicitly concatenated strings used as function args are now wrapped inside "
"parentheses ([#3307](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3307)) (22.12.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1124
msgid ""
"Correctly handle trailing commas that are inside a line's leading non-nested "
"parens ([#3370](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3370)) (22.12.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1126
msgid ""
"`--skip-string-normalization` / `-S` now prevents docstring prefixes from "
"being normalized as expected ([#3168](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/3168)) (since 22.8.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1128
msgid ""
"When using `--skip-magic-trailing-comma` or `-C`, trailing commas are "
"stripped from subscript expressions with more than 1 element ([#3209]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3209)) (22.8.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1130
msgid ""
"Implicitly concatenated strings inside a list, set, or tuple are now wrapped "
"inside parentheses ([#3162](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3162)) (22.8.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1132
msgid ""
"Fix a string merging/split issue when a comment is present in the middle of "
"implicitly concatenated strings on its own line ([#3227](https://github.com/"
"psf/black/pull/3227)) (22.8.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1134
msgid ""
"Docstring quotes are no longer moved if it would violate the line length "
"limit ([#3044](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3044), [#3430](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/3430)) (22.6.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1136
msgid ""
"Parentheses around return annotations are now managed ([#2990](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/2990)) (22.6.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1137
msgid ""
"Remove unnecessary parentheses around awaited objects ([#2991](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/2991)) (22.6.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1138
msgid ""
"Remove unnecessary parentheses in `with` statements ([#2926](https://github."
"com/psf/black/pull/2926)) (22.6.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1139
msgid ""
"Remove trailing newlines after code block open ([#3035](https://github.com/"
"psf/black/pull/3035)) (22.6.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1140
msgid ""
"Code cell separators `#%%` are now standardised to `# %%` ([#2919](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/2919)) (22.3.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1141
msgid ""
"Remove unnecessary parentheses from `except` statements ([#2939](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/2939)) (22.3.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1142
msgid ""
"Remove unnecessary parentheses from tuple unpacking in `for` loops ([#2945]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/2945)) (22.3.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1143
msgid ""
"Avoid magic-trailing-comma in single-element subscripts ([#2942](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/2942)) (22.3.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1144
msgid ""
"Fix a crash when a colon line is marked between `# fmt: off` and `# fmt: on` "
"([#3439](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3439))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1148
msgid ""
"Format hex codes in unicode escape sequences in string literals ([#2916]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/2916))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1150
msgid ""
"Improve performance on large expressions that contain many strings ([#3467]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3467))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1151
msgid ""
"Fix a crash in preview style with assert + parenthesized string ([#3415]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3415))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1152
msgid ""
"Fix crashes in preview style with walrus operators used in function return "
"annotations and except clauses ([#3423](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/3423))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1154
msgid ""
"Fix a crash in preview advanced string processing where mixed implicitly "
"concatenated regular and f-strings start with an empty span ([#3463](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/3463))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1156
msgid ""
"Fix a crash in preview advanced string processing where a standalone comment "
"is placed before a dict's value ([#3469](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/3469))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1158
msgid ""
"Fix an issue where extra empty lines are added when a decorator has `# fmt: "
"skip` applied or there is a standalone comment between decorators ([#3470]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3470))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1160
msgid ""
"Do not put the closing quotes in a docstring on a separate line, even if the "
"line is too long ([#3430](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3430))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1162
msgid ""
"Long values in dict literals are now wrapped in parentheses; correspondingly "
"unnecessary parentheses around short values in dict literals are now "
"removed; long string lambda values are now wrapped in parentheses ([#3440]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3440))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1165
msgid ""
"Fix two crashes in preview style involving edge cases with docstrings "
"([#3451](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3451))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1166
msgid ""
"Exclude string type annotations from improved string processing; fix crash "
"when the return type annotation is stringified and spans across multiple "
"lines ([#3462](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3462))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1168
msgid ""
"Wrap multiple context managers in parentheses when targeting Python 3.9+ "
"([#3489](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3489))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1169
msgid ""
"Fix several crashes in preview style with walrus operators used in `with` "
"statements or tuples ([#3473](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3473))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1171
msgid ""
"Fix an invalid quote escaping bug in f-string expressions where it produced "
"invalid code. Implicitly concatenated f-strings with different quotes can "
"now be merged or quote-normalized by changing the quotes used in "
"expressions. ([#3509](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3509))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1174
msgid ""
"Fix crash on `await (yield)` when Black is compiled with mypyc ([#3533]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3533))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1178
msgid ""
"Black now tries to infer its `--target-version` from the project metadata "
"specified in `pyproject.toml` ([#3219](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/3219))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1183
msgid ""
"Upgrade mypyc from `0.971` to `0.991` so mypycified _Black_ can be built on "
"armv7 ([#3380](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3380))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1185
msgid ""
"This also fixes some crashes while using compiled Black with a debug build "
"of CPython"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1187
msgid ""
"Drop specific support for the `tomli` requirement on 3.11 alpha releases, "
"working around a bug that would cause the requirement not to be installed on "
"any non-final Python releases ([#3448](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/3448))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1190
msgid ""
"Black now depends on `packaging` version `22.0` or later. This is required "
"for new functionality that needs to parse part of the project metadata "
"([#3219](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3219))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1195
msgid ""
"Calling `black --help` multiple times will return the same help contents "
"each time ([#3516](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3516))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1197
msgid ""
"Verbose logging now shows the values of `pyproject.toml` configuration "
"variables ([#3392](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3392))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1199
msgid ""
"Fix false symlink detection messages in verbose output due to using an "
"incorrect relative path to the project root ([#3385](https://github.com/psf/"
"black/pull/3385))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1204
msgid ""
"Move 3.11 CI to normal flow now that all dependencies support 3.11 ([#3446]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3446))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1205
msgid ""
"Docker: Add new `latest_prerelease` tag automation to follow latest black "
"alpha release on docker images ([#3465](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/3465))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1210
msgid ""
"Expand `vim-plug` installation instructions to offer more explicit options "
"([#3468](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3468))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1212
msgid "Version 22.12.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1216
msgid ""
"Enforce empty lines before classes and functions with sticky leading "
"comments ([#3302](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3302))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1217
msgid ""
"Reformat empty and whitespace-only files as either an empty file (if no "
"newline is present) or as a single newline character (if a newline is "
"present) ([#3348](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3348))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1219
msgid ""
"Implicitly concatenated strings used as function args are now wrapped inside "
"parentheses ([#3307](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3307))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1221
msgid ""
"For assignment statements, prefer splitting the right hand side if the left "
"hand side fits on a single line ([#3368](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/3368))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1223
msgid ""
"Correctly handle trailing commas that are inside a line's leading non-nested "
"parens ([#3370](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3370))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1228
msgid ""
"Fix incorrectly applied `.gitignore` rules by considering the `.gitignore` "
"location and the relative path to the target file ([#3338](https://github."
"com/psf/black/pull/3338))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1230
msgid ""
"Fix incorrectly ignoring `.gitignore` presence when more than one source "
"directory is specified ([#3336](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3336))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1235
msgid ""
"Parsing support has been added for walruses inside generator expression that "
"are passed as function args (for example, `any(match := my_re.match(text) "
"for text in texts)`) ([#3327](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3327))."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1241
msgid ""
"Vim plugin: Optionally allow using the system installation of Black via `let "
"g:black_use_virtualenv = 0`([#3309](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3309))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1244
msgid "Version 22.10.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1248
msgid ""
"Runtime support for Python 3.6 has been removed. Formatting 3.6 code will "
"still be supported until further notice."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1253
msgid ""
"Fix a crash when `# fmt: on` is used on a different block level than `# fmt: "
"off` ([#3281](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3281))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1258
msgid ""
"Fix a crash when formatting some dicts with parenthesis-wrapped long string "
"keys ([#3262](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3262))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1263
msgid ""
"`.ipynb_checkpoints` directories are now excluded by default ([#3293]"
"(https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3293))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1264
msgid ""
"Add `--skip-source-first-line` / `-x` option to ignore the first line of "
"source code while formatting ([#3299](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/3299))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1269
msgid ""
"Executables made with PyInstaller will no longer crash when formatting "
"several files at once on macOS. Native x86-64 executables for macOS are "
"available once again. ([#3275](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3275))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1272
msgid ""
"Hatchling is now used as the build backend. This will not have any effect "
"for users who install Black with its wheels from PyPI. ([#3233](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/3233))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1274
msgid ""
"Faster compiled wheels are now available for CPython 3.11 ([#3276](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/pull/3276))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1278
msgid ""
"Windows style (CRLF) newlines will be preserved ([#3257](https://github.com/"
"psf/black/pull/3257))."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1282
msgid ""
"Vim plugin: add flag (`g:black_preview`) to enable/disable the preview style "
"([#3246](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3246))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1283
msgid ""
"Update GitHub Action to support formatting of Jupyter Notebook files via a "
"`jupyter` option ([#3282](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3282))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1285
msgid ""
"Update GitHub Action to support use of version specifiers (e.g. `<23`) for "
"Black version ([#3265](https://github.com/psf/black/pull/3265))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1288
msgid "Version 22.8.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1292
msgid ""
"Python 3.11 is now supported, except for _blackd_ as aiohttp does not "
"support 3.11 as of publishing ([#3234](https://github.com/psf/black/"
"pull/3234))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1294
msgid ""
"This is the last release that supports running _Black_ on Python 3.6 "
"(formatting 3.6 code will continue to be supported until further notice)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.md:1296
